Map Metadata¶

reamber.algorithms.analysis.describe.meta.mapMetadata(m: O2JMapObj, s: O2JMapSetObj, unicode: bool) → str¶
reamber.algorithms.analysis.describe.meta.mapMetadata(m: OsuMapObj, s: None, unicode: bool) → str
reamber.algorithms.analysis.describe.meta.mapMetadata(m: QuaMapObj, s: None, unicode: bool) → str
reamber.algorithms.analysis.describe.meta.mapMetadata(m: SMMapObj, s: SMMapSetObj, unicode: bool) → str

Grabs the map metadata

Parameters

  • m – The Map Object

  • s – The Map Set Object, not required for some types

  • unicode – Whether to try to find the unicode or non-unicode. This doesn’t try to convert unicode to ascii, it just looks for if there’s an available translation.

Returns
